File: A medical worker tests for the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - The World Health Organization is urging European governments to take decisive action against COVID-19. They want to break the chain of transmission as infections continue to soar. READ:Â NICD says difficult to predict second COVID-19 wave Europe surpassed a hundred thousand daily reported COVID-19 cases for the first time on Thursday. France, Russia and the UK are seeing no respite from mounting numbers of infections. On Monday, British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson, is expect to unveil details of new restrictions to slow the spread of coronavirus. The WHO says governments trying to avoid lockdown while also breaking the chain of transmission could find this to be difficult.